    <summary>AI cockpit for architects — drives Revit, Blender, AutoCAD, 3ds Max and Speckle from one chat.</summary>
    <description><![CDATA[
ArchHub is a free, open-source desktop app that lets architects drive
Revit, Blender, AutoCAD, 3ds Max and Speckle from a single chat
interface. Useful conversations save as Skills — copy-paste shareable
JSON workflow graphs that run again on demand.

## Features

- Chat drives every tool natively (no copying code, no manual exports)
- Vision input — paste a sketch, get a 3D mass
- Skills you save and share (ComfyUI-style JSON)
- Sketch → production pipeline (six chained LLM stages)
- Multi-LLM, BYO key (OpenRouter OAuth, Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, local Ollama)
- Cloud-synced Skills via your private GitHub
- First-run wizard, in-app auto-update, click-only setup

## License

MIT. Source: https://github.com/Fargaly/ArchHub
    ]]></description>
